ase sensing angles with a much lower\ncomputational complexity than the beampattern matching design. We show that by\nexploiting the capability of canceling the interference caused by the radar\nsignals, the case with Type-II receivers results in better sensing performance\nthan that with Type-I receivers and other conventional designs.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sat, 24 Apr 2021 03:16:58 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sun, 5 Dec 2021 01:46:42 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Sat, 23 Apr 2022 03:02:14 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Sat, 25 Mar 2023 03:58:08 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-03-28"}
